The paper discusses a stochastic model for electron transfer in microbial communities, which involves the exchange of electrons between neighboring cells. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including modeling and simulation (cs.MS), systems and control (cs.SY), network science (cs.NE), and bioinformatics (cs.BIO). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for electron-based communication networks in microbial communities, which could be relevant to the sub-field of social and information networks (cs.SI).
